    <paragraphs>
        <title>Basic operations</title>

        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>Use a star for multiplication. For example, <m>3x</m> should be entered as <c>3*x</c>.</li>
                <li>Use a caret (^) for raising something to a power: for example, <m>x^2</m> should be entered as <c>x^2</c></li>
                <li><m>x^{-2}</m> should be entered as <c>x^(-2)</c></li>
                <li><m>\displaystyle x^{\frac{1}{3}}</m> should be entered as <c>x^(1/3)</c></li>
                <li>Brackets are important to group terms in an expression.</li>
            </ul>

        </p>

